 {"id":"bd-yx9r.19.1","title":"Implement actor model, mailbox, and actor runtime public parity","description":"Port the public actor-facing surface: actor APIs, mailbox/message lifecycle, actor runtime hooks, and integration with existing task/channel/runtime machinery. The current ANSI C work is too thin to count as crate-level actor parity.","design":"This should be treated as a user-facing framework layer with strong lifecycle and logging guarantees, not just a few helper structs over channels.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public actor APIs and mailbox semantics are implemented and documented.\\nB. Unit/integration tests cover message ordering, mailbox backpressure, actor shutdown, and failure paths.\\nC. Logged scenarios show actor lifecycle, failure, and restart-precondition artifacts.","notes":"Depends on runtime, channel, and capability/evidence work.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:03.272967139Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:43.124303419Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["actor","crate-parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:28.590557225Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.19","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:03.272967139Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:30.027120754Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:31.488751743Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:43.123664600Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.19.2","title":"Implement gen_server semantics and supervision/restart policy parity","description":"Port gen_server-style call/cast/reply semantics and the supervision layer: child specs, restart strategies, escalation rules, and failure containment. This is one of the clearest user-facing framework gaps versus the Rust crate.","design":"The bead should be explicit about restart semantics, budget/cancel interactions, and the logging/reporting story when supervised trees fail or churn.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public gen_server and supervision APIs exist with documented restart and escalation semantics.\\nB. Unit and scenario tests cover call/cast paths, child restart strategies, escalation, and negative/failure cases.\\nC. Logged e2e flows show supervised tree startup, crash, restart, escalation, and final artifact summaries.","notes":"Depends on S1 and on the runtime/evidence foundations so failures are diagnosable.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:05.684145905Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:44.755676505Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","gen-server","supervision"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:32.953989696Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.19","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:05.684145905Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.19.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:44.754717751Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:34.425222272Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.19.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:35.908559500Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.2","title":"Audit feature/profile/platform matrix drift versus upstream crate contract","description":"The upstream crate contract is not just modules; it also includes feature gates, browser/native exclusions, platform splits, and profile combinations. The ANSI C port currently mixes profile work, deferred-surface docs, and selective stubs without a crate-level compatibility matrix.","design":"Produce a feature/profile/platform matrix that maps upstream cargo features and target splits to ANSI C profile flags, native/browser restrictions, missing capabilities, and fail-closed behavior expectations. This should expose where the C tree needs new compile-time guards, runtime gates, or explicit not-yet-supported diagnostics.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Upstream feature/platform combinations are mapped to ANSI C equivalents or explicit gaps.\\nB. Browser/native/server/tls/database/grpc/networking restrictions are called out concretely.\\nC. The matrix identifies missing compile-time and runtime fail-closed checks needed before parity claims.\\nD. Downstream beads can depend on this matrix instead of rediscovering compatibility rules.","notes":"Use upstream lib.rs compile errors, target-specific modules, and README install/usage guidance as the contract source.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:16.800157869Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T00:48:39.943180001Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T00:48:39.889274325Z","close_reason":"Completed: updated docs/PROFILE_RESOURCE_CLASS_CAPABILITY_MATRIX.md to include the BROWSER profile already present in code plus an upstream-vs-C feature/platform drift audit and missing fail-closed checks","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","features","profiles"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:16.800157869Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:44.037051653Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-yx9r.3","title":"Expand verification and e2e contract for reopened crate-level surfaces","description":"The old evidence model was sufficient for kernel semantics but not for crate-level parity. Higher surfaces like HTTP, web, TLS, service layers, distributed flows, and database/messaging all need richer integration and operator-facing evidence than the existing kernel/test harnesses provide.","design":"Define the verification contract for reopened surfaces: required unit suites, integration tests, conformance or semantic-fixture lanes where applicable, deterministic smoke packs, detailed JSONL logs, artifact manifests, replay hints, failure triage summaries, and cross-profile/browser/native coverage expectations.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Each reopened subsystem family has a default evidence pattern before implementation starts.\\nB. E2E expectations include happy path, degraded path, failure path, and artifact/logging requirements.\\nC. Feature-gated and platform-specific modules specify when differential fixtures are required and when justified exclusions are acceptable.\\nD. Final crate-level parity acceptance depends on this contract.","notes":"This task should replace any implicit assumption that 'unit tests plus make test' are enough for application/protocol/distributed surfaces.","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:17.394115417Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T02:35:26.749759199Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","e2e","verification"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:17.394115417Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:44.695758025Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
